A: Fixed-size stack buffer. Input exceeding buffer overwrites adjacent stack
memory including return address. Attacker crafts input overwriting return
address with shellcode address or ROP gadget. Mitigations: bounds checking,
ASLR, stack canaries, NX/DEP.

